inputs.falcon:
SPARK | VISUAL LANGUAGE SHEET  
Live Circuit – “Nervous System”

--------------------------------------------------
1. ROOT TOKENS (Tailwind plugin or CSS variables)

:root {
  --void: #050505;           /* bg */
  --matrix: #00FF41;        /* success */
  --alert: #FF2E4C;          /* failure */
  --process: #FFD400;        /* processing */
  --mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  --scan-speed: 6s;
  --glow-blur: 0 0 4px;
}

--------------------------------------------------
2. GLOBAL SCENE CLASSES

.scene {
  @apply min-h-screen bg-void text-matrix font-mono text-xs leading-none select-none;
  background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(
    0deg,
    rgba(0,255,65,0.03) 0,
    transparent 1px,
    transparent 2px,
    rgba(0,255,65,0.03) 3px
  );
  animation: scan var(--scan-speed) linear infinite;
}

@keyframes scan {
  0%   { background-position: 0 0; }
  100% { background-position: 0 100vh; }
}

--------------------------------------------------
3. WIRE (THE NERVOUS SYSTEM)

<wire> is an inline SVG <path> inside a <div class="wire">.

.wire {
  @apply relative block w-full h-full;
}
.wire svg {
  @apply w-full h-full;
}
.wire path {
  stroke-width: 2;
  stroke-linecap: round;
  fill: none;
  stroke: var(--matrix);
  filter: drop-shadow(var(--glow-blur) var(--matrix));
  transition: stroke 0.3s ease;
}

/* STATES */
.wire[data-state="success"] path {
  stroke: var(--matrix);
  filter: drop-shadow(var(--glow-blur) var(--matrix));
}
.wire[data-state="failure"] path {
  stroke: var(--alert);
  filter: drop-shadow(var(--glow-blur) var(--alert));
  animation: blink 0.4s steps(2) infinite;
}
.wire[data-state="processing"] path {
  stroke: var(--process);
  filter: drop-shadow(var(--glow-blur) var(--process));
}

/* Pulsing light along the wire */
.wire[data-state="processing"] path {
  stroke-dasharray: 12 8;
  stroke-dashoffset: 0;
  animation: flow 1s linear infinite;
}
@keyframes flow {
  to { stroke-dashoffset: -20; }
}
@keyframes blink {
  50% { opacity: 0; }
}

--------------------------------------------------
4. FRAMER MOTION VARIANTS (React)

const wireStates = {
  idle:   { filter: 'drop-shadow(0 0 4px #00FF41)' },
  success:{ filter: 'drop-shadow(0 0 12px #00FF41)' },
  failure:{
    filter: 'drop-shadow(0 0 20px #FF2E4C)',
    opacity: [1,0,1],
    transition: { repeat: Infinity, duration: 0.4 }
  },
  processing:{
    strokeDashoffset: [0, -20],
    transition: { repeat: Infinity, ease: 'linear', duration: 1 }
  }
};

Usage:
<motion.path
  variants={wireStates}
  animate={state}          // 'idle' | 'success' | 'failure' | 'processing'
/>

--------------------------------------------------
5. TEXT & CURSOR FX

.blink::after {
  content: '▋';
  @apply inline-block text-matrix animate-pulse;
}

.text-glow {
  text-shadow: 0 0 4px var(--matrix), 0 0 8px var(--matrix);
}

--------------------------------------------------
6. JIT UTILITY SHORTCUTS (Tailwind)

Add to tailwind.config.js

theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: {
      void: 'var(--void)',
      matrix: 'var(--matrix)',
      alert: 'var(--alert)',
      process: 'var(--process)',
    },
    fontFamily: { mono: ['var(--mono)'] },
    animation: {
      scan: 'scan var(--scan-speed) linear infinite',
      flow: 'flow 1s linear infinite',
      blink: 'blink 0.4s steps(2) infinite',
    },
  },
}

--------------------------------------------------
7. IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

- Use SVG pathLength="100" for consistent dash calculations.  
- Keep wires inside a <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100"> so Framer’s dashoffset animations scale responsively.  
- Attach state to the parent .wire, not the SVG, so you can swap colors & filters in one place.  
- For “point of break” on failure, split the path at the fault coordinate and animate two separate <motion.path> elements with stagger = 0.  

SPARK | END OF SPEC

